PRIMARY: Two Just Stop Oil protesters, Jennifer Kowalski (28) and Cole Macdonald (22), used angle grinders to break through Stansted Airport's fence at 5am and sprayed orange paint on two private jets using fire extinguishers. The action caused Â£52,000 in cleanup costs and disrupted 75 flights for 38 minutes, affecting thousands of passengers. Both denied charges of criminal damage and interfering with national infrastructure.

SECONDARY: No secondary protest actions mentioned.

OTHER FOCAL: The article notes Taylor Swift's private jet was not at the airport despite Just Stop Oil's claims it had landed hours before the incident.

TONE: The article maintains a neutral, factual tone focusing on legal proceedings and damage costs.
